        <title>Hardening Edge Infrastructure: pfSense &amp; VLAN Segmentation</title>
        <link>http://localhost:1313/post/infrastructure/pfsense-hardening/</link>
        <pubDate>Sat, 27 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/infrastructure/pfsense-hardening/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="http://localhost:1313/post/infrastructure/pfsense-hardening/cover.webp" alt="Featured image of post Hardening Edge Infrastructure: pfSense &amp; VLAN Segmentation" /&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;infrastructure-layout&#34;&gt;Infrastructure Layout
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;To maintain OPSEC and isolate exploit testing, Iâ€™ve implemented a multi-VLAN structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VLAN 10 (Management):&lt;/strong&gt; Isolated for primary workstations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VLAN 20 (Lab):&lt;/strong&gt; Where the &amp;ldquo;vulnerable&amp;rdquo; targets live.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VLAN 30 (Red):&lt;/strong&gt; Dedicated for C2 traffic and egress testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;firewall-rules&#34;&gt;Firewall Rules
